From: Jerry Huang <Chang-Ming.Huang@freescale.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Feb 2010 17:44:26 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 134/148] sdhci: add abort to multiple block transfer

ABORT command has to be send to stop multiblock transfer.

Signed-off-by: Jerry Huang <Chang-Ming.Huang@freescale.com>
Signed-off-by: Dipen Dudhat <dipen.dudhat@freescale.com>
[Cleanly applied the FSL SDK 2.0.3 patch:
"kernel-2.6.30-sdhci-add-abort-to-multiple-block-transfer.patch"]
Integrated-by: Yuri Nedel <Yuri.Nedel@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/mmc/host/sdhci.c |    3 +++
 drivers/mmc/host/sdhci.h |    1 +
 2 files changed, 4 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/mmc/host/sdhci.c b/drivers/mmc/host/sdhci.c
index 9d4fdfa..1dd4fb6 100644
--- a/drivers/mmc/host/sdhci.c
+++ b/drivers/mmc/host/sdhci.c
@@ -930,6 +930,9 @@ static void sdhci_send_command(struct sdhci_host *host, struct mmc_command *cmd)
 	if (cmd->data)
 		flags |= SDHCI_CMD_DATA;
 
+	if (host->mrq->data && (cmd == host->mrq->data->stop))
+		flags = flags | SDHCI_CMD_ABORT;
+
 	sdhci_writew(host, SDHCI_MAKE_CMD(cmd->opcode, flags), SDHCI_COMMAND);
 }
 
diff --git a/drivers/mmc/host/sdhci.h b/drivers/mmc/host/sdhci.h
index 842f46f..4f8ddd5 100644
--- a/drivers/mmc/host/sdhci.h
+++ b/drivers/mmc/host/sdhci.h
@@ -41,6 +41,7 @@
 #define  SDHCI_CMD_CRC		0x08
 #define  SDHCI_CMD_INDEX	0x10
 #define  SDHCI_CMD_DATA		0x20
+#define  SDHCI_CMD_ABORT	0xC0
 
 #define  SDHCI_CMD_RESP_NONE	0x00
 #define  SDHCI_CMD_RESP_LONG	0x01
